<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 28 at 9:51PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Colder with Light Snow...
A new cold front is advancing southward through Central and into
Southwest Montana late this evening into the early morning hours.
The front will produce areas of light snow lower temperatures
back below zero. Expect visibility reduced to around 1/2 mile in
snow. Northerly winds will increase with the passing front,
producing wind chill values of 5 to 20 degrees below zero. Use
caution if traveling, and carry a vehicle safety kit including
extra warm clothing. Snow will continue off and on at times
overnight while temperatures continued to lower into the single
digits and teens below zero.</description>
